# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# combined — __rpow__, __rlshift__, __rrshift__ across all 10 asyncio subjects
#
# Covers the full matrix: 10 classes x 3 methods = 30 rows.
# __rpow__: false for all 10 — reflected power is not defined.
# __rlshift__: false for all 10 — reflected left shift is not defined.
# __rrshift__: false for all 10 — reflected right shift is not defined.
# All 30 values are false.
# asyncio types are designed for coroutine-based concurrency — their entire
#   API surface is expressed through await, async with, async for, and
#   explicit method calls. Neither forward nor reflected power or shift
#   operators appear anywhere in the asyncio type hierarchy.
# asyncio.Queue note: Queue is an ordered item store. It does not use
#   __lshift__/__rlshift__ as a pipe/push operator or __rshift__/__rrshift__
#   as a dequeue/pipe operator; it manages items solely through put()/get()
#   coroutine calls.
# asyncio.Semaphore note: the permit counter is a positive integer, but it
#   is fully encapsulated. Neither power nor shift is exposed through any
#   part of the API from either side of the operator.
# This wave continues the unbroken all-false run from wave 656 (__call__/
#   __len__/__getitem__) through wave 664 (__rpow__/__rlshift__/__rrshift__)
#   — nine consecutive waves of 100% false results for asyncio types.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

